Guinea-Bissau has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Guinea-Bissau, see Return to the UK
Local measures
The Bissau-Guinean authorities have introduced new measures in relation to coronavirus, including closing all land and sea borders and commercial air links. A state of emergency is in place. Public transport has been suspended to stop the spread of the virus. Only essential businesses (food, medical supplies) are operating. The government has set up a coronavirus hotline that you can call on: 1919 or 2020.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
